<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,345,1067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,963,989]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[351,688,964,989]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Borodinellaceae" genus="Smaragdina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulotrichales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">
<emphasis box="[351,688,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Smaragdina quadrimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" box="[843,1077,964,990]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Borodinellaceae" genus="Smaragdina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ulotrichales" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="nigrosignatus">
<emphasis box="[843,1033,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">S. nigrosignatus</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
from Fuxian but can easily be differentiated by the color pattern of elytra and the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[198,1175,1040,1067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="etymology">
